deck: The Red Panda's secret headquarters.
description:
Overview

The Lair is the secret underground headquarters of the Red Panda and the Flying Squirrel. Located far underneath August Fenwick's mansion, it is where the Red Panda creates his technology, hones his fighting skills, performs his experiments and stores his equipment. Man-sized pneumatic tubes carry him and the Flying Squirrel to and from various points around Toronto.
name: The Lair

volume_credits.name: Red Panda: Mask of the Red Panda

deck: Toronto newspaper owned by August Fenwick.
description:
Overview

The "Toronto Daily Chronicle" was once considered a dirt-sheet, far behind the "Toronto Sentinel" in readership. Over the years, after being purchased by Toronto billionaire August Fenwick, the paper earned a great deal of respectability. Under the leadership of editor-in-chief Timothy J. Pearly, the "Chronicle" hired away the "Sentinel's" star reporter, Jack Peters, and enjoyed a long life at the top of the news game.
name: Toronto Daily Chronicle Building
